parameters:
"...What's that? I can hear some strange water sounds coming
from behind the door. It can't be rainwater seeping in, can
it?"

"What the hell is this!? The hallway is flooded! Is it
raining so hard that the drainage can't keep up!?"

"Hey, it's me!! The basement is flooding! Hurry up and
evacuate the guests!! And that includes all the women!!"

"That's why I said we should call it off today... I can't
just stand around. I need to help with the evacuation too."

"We have staff holding umbrellas on standby upstairs! Please
evacuate calmly and without rushing!"

"Sigh... I was looking forward to violating a new girl
today."

"Now, now, there's always time to violate women. Right now,
your safety is what's most important."

"Damn it! How long do you expect me to wait! Move it, old
men! Let me evacuate first!"

"Please stop, young master! If you run up the stairs with
wet shoes... Ahh!"

"What are you doing, young master!? Ahh, he's stretched out
on the floor... We need to call an ambulance."

I really wanted to make sure Makoto made it out safely, but
without an umbrella in the pouring rain, I had no choice but
to return home in the end.

After warming up my wet body with a shower, I decided to
call Makoto under the pretense of worrying about the heavy
rain. If she escaped from that basement, she should be at
home by now.

After several rings, I was about to hang up, but just before
I did, Makoto finally answered the phone. It seems she was
also taking a shower at home, just like me.

We talked about the weather, but I didn't feel any
particular sense of discomfort during the conversation. The
plan was a success, and it seems Makoto managed to escape
from that basement.

After ending the call with Makoto, I crawled into bed
feeling a strong sense of accomplishment. That day, I spent
a quiet night listening to the rain tapering off.

"What? The liquor I ordered hasn't arrived? Give me a break,
today we have some VIPs over."

"What kind of liquor? Oh, we should have that in stock.
Check it first before calling me. I'm hanging up now, make
sure you handle it."

"(Ah, that was close... If he hadn't been on the phone, I
would've definitely run into the man with sunglasses.)"

"(I think Makoto probably went further inside... but I can't
get through this way because of that guy.)"

"(Can't be helped... I need to look around and see if
there's another way to go.)"

(There's only one man with sunglasses in front of the door.
Should I take a gamble and rush in?)

*Note: If you select the text in \c[10]red\c[0], it will
result in a \c[10]failed conquest\c[0].
Are you sure about this choice?

"What's with this guy... He suddenly appeared and attacked
me... But he's ridiculously weak, saved me the trouble..."

"Huh? This guy is Asahi's childhood friend, isn't he. I see,
he recklessly came to save her."

"What a pain in the ass... Got irritated, so I guess I'll go
outside and beat him up a bit."

(No, this is no good! It's too reckless! I need to act
calmly to make sure I can definitely save Makoto!)

(No, this is no good. It's too reckless. I need to act
calmly to make sure I can definitely save Makoto!)

(It seems the path continues further in. Maybe it's okay to
check this room later.)

(The room next to number 1 is number 4. I wonder if the
person who assigned the room numbers made a mistake?)

(It seems the path continues further in. Maybe it's okay to
check this room later.)

(It seems the path continues further in. Maybe it's okay to
check this room later.)

(It seems the path continues further in. Maybe I can check
this room later.)

(With the card key I obtained earlier, I should probably be
able to open this door...)

(Yes, the door opened! Let's go ahead and see what's beyond
it right away!)

(This door is locked and won't open. It seems like I need a
card key.)

(It seems the path continues further in. Maybe I can check
this room later.)
